文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_040_chunk1
证据片段: Mechanical joints between Zircaloy and nickel-bearing alloys, mainly the Zircaloy-4/Inconel-600 combination, were exposed to water at 232 and 271°C to study hydriding of Zircaloy in contact with a dissimilar metal.

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_040_chunk1
证据片段: Mechanical joints between Zircaloy and nickel-bearing alloys, mainly the Zircaloy-4/Inconel-600 combination, were exposed to water at 232 and 271°C to study hydriding of Zircaloy in contact with a dissimilar metal.

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_040_chunk1
证据片段: Accelerated hydriding of the Zircaloy occurred at both temperatures.

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_040_chunk1
证据片段: At 232° the dissolved hydrogen level of the water was over ten times that at 271°C.

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_040_chunk1
证据片段: At 271°C the initially high hydrogen ingress rate decreased rapidly as exposure time increased and was effectively shut off in about 25 days.

文献ID: STP824-EB-Zirconium in the Nuclear Industry_6th Volume_040_chunk1
证据片段: Severely hydrided Zircaloy components successfully withstood thermal cycling and mechanical testing.
